<%# Star rating, 0–5 with half-stars.
    HOW IT WORKS: two identical rows of five stars are stacked.
    The bottom row is dim; the top row is blood red and clipped
    to a width matching the rating (e.g. 3.5 / 5 → 70%). This
    handles halves (and any decimal) with zero JavaScript.
    "size" is optional: pass size: 'lg' for the hero/review page. %>
<span class="stars <%= typeof size !== 'undefined' && size === 'lg' ? 'stars--lg' : '' %>"
      role="img" aria-label="Rated <%= rating %> out of 5 stars">
  <span class="stars-track" aria-hidden="true">★★★★★</span>
  <span class="stars-fill" aria-hidden="true" style="width: <%= (rating / 5) * 100 %>%">★★★★★</span>
</span>
